Make GiNaC::constant::calchash() deterministic across process runs, same bug as
ginac-deterministic-hash-seed.patch but in a different spot.

constant::calchash() does NOT go through make_hash_seed() (already fixed by the
sibling patch) - it has its own, independent, inline copy of the exact same
buggy computation: it hashes the *address* of the RTTI type-name string
(typeid(*this).name()), which moves every process run under ASLR. Since every
built-in GiNaC constant (Pi, Catalan, Euler, ...) is the SAME C++ type
(GiNaC::constant), this address is shared by all of them, and it is XORed with
each constant's own `serial` to tell them apart - but the ASLR-dependent
address still makes every constant's hash (and hence its sort position
relative to every other GiNaC type inside a sum/product) non-deterministic
across runs. This was found via citools/test_all_tutorial_scripts.py: run it
twice with --keep-outdirs and diff the generated _ccode/*.c files - several
tutorial scripts using axisymmetric coordinates (which introduce a factor of
Pi into the weak form) showed a "2*(...)" vs "-2*-(...)" sign-convention flip
between runs, always traced back to Pi. See branch deterministic_codegen.

--- a/ginac/constant.cpp
+++ b/ginac/constant.cpp
@@ -20,6 +20,7 @@
  */

 #include "constant.h"
+#include "hash_seed.h"
 #include "numeric.h"
 #include "ex.h"
 #include "archive.h"
@@ -211,8 +212,10 @@ bool constant::is_equal_same_type(const basic & other) const

 unsigned constant::calchash() const
 {
-	const void* typeid_this = (const void*)typeid(*this).name();
-	hashvalue = golden_ratio_hash((uintptr_t)typeid_this ^ serial);
+	// pyoomph: use the same deterministic (mangled-name-based) type hash seed as
+	// basic::calchash() and friends, instead of the ASLR-dependent RTTI pointer
+	// this used to hash directly - see ginac-deterministic-hash-seed.patch.
+	hashvalue = golden_ratio_hash(make_hash_seed(typeid(*this)) ^ serial);

 	setflag(status_flags::hash_calculated);

